Phase 1 - Core API Agent summary.

The phase-1 profiles API module shipped in commit 87f1fe5
("phase-1(api/profiles): companion profile CRUD, availability, photo refs")
and the wire contract was published in `app/api/profiles/CONTRACT.md`.
The Foundations re-pin in commit 3a6e048 (Next 15 + ESLint 9 + async
`cookies()`) brought the slice forward; the auth gate at
`app/api/profiles/_lib/auth.ts` already `await`s
`createSupabaseServerClient()` so no further changes were required this
phase. This re-invocation re-audited the slice end-to-end and ran the
gates that exist locally - everything is still green and no code change
was needed.

WHAT I DID

- **Re-audited every file in the Core API agent's owned area** against
  the phase-1 task list and the CORE PRODUCT RULES. The owned slice for
  this phase is exactly `/app/api/profiles/**` plus the published
  contract:

  - `app/api/profiles/_lib/auth.ts` - `requireAuth()` and
    `requireCompanionMode()`. Re-reads the Supabase session on every
    call (server-side authority), loads the mirrored `public.users`
    row, and gates companion-only writes on `is_companion=true` (CORE
    PRODUCT RULE #5 - one account, two modes - enforced at the API
    boundary, with `users_at_least_one_mode` CHECK in the DB as
    belt-and-braces).
  - `app/api/profiles/_lib/db.ts` - request-scoped Supabase client
    factory; `LooseSupabaseClient` cast to side-step a known
    `@supabase/postgrest-js` row-inference collapse against the frozen
    `Database` type. Results are re-narrowed to the published `*Row`
    types from `@/lib/types` at the boundary; RLS remains the
    authoritative fence.
  - `app/api/profiles/_lib/errors.ts` - the stable `ApiErrorCode` union
    and JSON envelope every endpoint returns (`unauthenticated`,
    `forbidden`, `not_found`, `invalid_input`, `conflict`,
    `companion_mode_required`, `internal_error`).
  - `app/api/profiles/_lib/parse.ts` - one-shot zod-validating JSON
    body reader; converts `ZodError` into a 400 with
    `details = err.flatten()` so the Frontend can render field-level
    errors.
  - `app/api/profiles/_lib/validators.ts` - zod schemas whose bounds
    mirror the DB CHECK constraints (`rate_cents` 500..20000,
    `service_radius_m` 500..100000, `meal_types` non-empty subset of
    the published `MEAL_TYPES`, GeoJSON Point with WGS-84 ranges,
    HH:MM[:SS] times, IANA timezone, `end_time > start_time` refinement
    on availability create/update). CORE PRODUCT RULE #1 (lunch and
    dinner only) is enforced here by typing `meal_type` against the
    `MealType` literal union from `@/lib/types`.
  - `app/api/profiles/_lib/types.ts` - the published wire shapes
    (`OwnCompanionProfileDTO`, `PublicCompanionProfileDTO`,
    `AvailabilityDTO`) plus mappers from the DB Row types. The owner
    DTO joins `display_name`, `email`, `avatar_path` from `public.users`
    so the profile-setup screen has everything it needs in one round-trip.
  - `app/api/profiles/me/route.ts` - GET/PUT/DELETE for the caller's
    own companion profile. The PUT path deliberately reads-then-
    inserts-or-updates (instead of `.upsert()`) so a caller cannot
    silently overwrite owner-only columns
    (`verification_status`, `verified_at`,
    `stripe_connect_account_id`, `stripe_payouts_enabled`,
    `avg_rating`, `rating_count`). DELETE is hard-delete; the
    `availability.companion_user_id` FK has `ON DELETE CASCADE` per
    the frozen schema, so windows go with the profile. Bookings refer
    to `users.id` rather than the companion profile, so historical
    bookings are preserved.
  - `app/api/profiles/[id]/route.ts` - public read of a verified
    companion. Verification gating (CORE PRODUCT RULE #9 - unverified
    companions cannot be discovered or booked) is enforced by RLS
    (`companion_profiles_select_verified` in
    `supabase/migrations/20260515000600_rls.sql`); this layer maps a
    missing row to 404 without distinguishing "does not exist" from
    "exists but unverified" so we don't leak existence. Auth required;
    anonymous discovery is out of scope for the MVP.
  - `app/api/profiles/me/availability/route.ts` - GET / POST. POST
    pre-checks for an existing companion-profile row and returns
    `409 conflict` with a clean message ("set up your profile first")
    instead of letting a Postgres FK violation bubble up.
  - `app/api/profiles/me/availability/[id]/route.ts` - PUT / DELETE.
    Mismatched ids return 404 (not 403) so callers cannot probe other
    users' window ids; ownership is double-fenced with both an
    `eq('companion_user_id', caller.userId)` clause and the
    `availability_update_self` / `availability_delete_self` RLS
    policies. PUT runs an extra read-and-merge ordering check when
    only one side of `start_time`/`end_time` is patched, so a partial
    update can never land an inverted window.
  - `app/api/profiles/me/photo/route.ts` - reference-only photo
    endpoint. The actual upload of avatar bytes is owned by Auth &
    Identity (`lib/auth/storage.ts#uploadAvatar`); this endpoint sets
    or clears `users.avatar_path`. The supplied path is required to
    live under the caller's `<userId>/` prefix - the convention the
    Auth uploader uses - so a caller cannot point their avatar at
    someone else's object.
  - `app/api/profiles/CONTRACT.md` - frozen wire contract for the
    Frontend agent. Endpoint shapes, status codes, error envelope, the
    `ApiErrorCode` union, all DTOs, and the GeoJSON Point convention
    are documented in one place.

- **Verified the slice still builds under the Foundations rebase** (Next
  15 + ESLint 9 + async `cookies()` in commit 3a6e048 and the Database
  / Auth re-pins in 8422021 / b336861). The auth gate awaits
  `createSupabaseServerClient()` so the `cookies()` async change is
  already absorbed; route handler signatures remain Next-15-compatible
  (synchronous `params` is still accepted, just deprecation-warned, so
  no signature change is needed for Phase 1).

- **Confirmed CORE PRODUCT RULE coverage at this layer:**
  - #1 (lunch and dinner only): every meal-type field is typed against
    `MealType` from `@/lib/types`; zod rejects anything else.
  - #5 (one account, two modes): `requireCompanionMode()` blocks every
    write that touches companion-owned state.
  - #9 (unverified companions are non-discoverable / non-bookable):
    `GET /api/profiles/[id]` returns 404 when RLS hides the row, and
    the API surface deliberately offers no path to set
    `verification_status` / `verified_at`.
  - The API never accepts `stripe_connect_account_id` or
    `stripe_payouts_enabled` writes (those are Payments-agent
    territory) and never accepts `avg_rating` / `rating_count` writes
    (those are roll-ups maintained by the reviews module in a later
    phase).

- **Ran the gates that exist locally**:
  - `npm run type-check` - clean.
  - `npm run lint` - clean.
  - `npm run test:unit` - 5 files, 50/50 passing. Includes the
    QA-agent's mocked `requireAuth` / `requireCompanionMode` branch
    coverage (`tests/unit/auth-gate.test.ts`), the profile validator
    bounds (`tests/unit/profile-validators.test.ts`), and the
    JSON-body parser branch coverage
    (`tests/unit/parse-json-body.test.ts`).
  - `npm run test:integration` and `npm run test:rls` - the relevant
    suites exist (`tests/integration/profiles.test.ts`,
    `tests/rls/policies.test.ts`) but `describe.skipIf` out without
    `TEST_SUPABASE_*` env vars, which are operator-provisioned. Same
    blocker the Database and Auth agents recorded.

- **No code changes** were necessary in this re-run. Phase-1 Core API
  was already delivered in 87f1fe5 and remains green. The artifact this
  run produces is this log + the commit recording it.

WHAT I COULD NOT DO

- **End-to-end exercise the endpoints against a live Supabase project.**
  `.env.local` still ships placeholder Supabase URL / anon / service-role
  values (Foundations / founder territory), so an actual HTTP request
  against the route handlers cannot be authorized today. Verification
  is currently typecheck + unit tests + an audit against the published
  schema and RLS policies. Same blocker the Database and Auth agents
  recorded.

- **Run the integration and RLS suites against a disposable Supabase
  project.** Both suites need `TEST_SUPABASE_URL`,
  `TEST_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY`, and `TEST_SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY` pointed
  at a *disposable* project (deliberately not dev). They `skipIf` out
  without them.

- **Build the rest of the Core API surface** (`/search`, `/requests`,
  `/bookings`, `/messaging`, `/reviews`, `/notifications`). These are
  not phase-1 scope per the execution plan and per this run's task
  list. They will land in later phases against the same patterns this
  module establishes (auth gate, zod validators with DB-mirrored
  bounds, RLS-as-final-fence, no writes to roll-up or owner-only
  columns).

- **Wire profile changes into transactional emails.** `notifications`
  is a future Core API module; the Integrations agent owns
  `lib/email`. Out of phase-1 scope.

INTERFACES PUBLISHED

The frozen wire contract for the Frontend agent (unchanged since 87f1fe5):

- **Document**: `app/api/profiles/CONTRACT.md` - endpoint shapes,
  status codes, error envelope, error-code table, GeoJSON convention,
  and the full DTO appendix.

- **HTTP surface** (all routes are JSON in / JSON out, all require an
  authenticated caller via the request-scoped Supabase client):
  - `GET    /api/profiles/me`                          - own companion profile
  - `PUT    /api/profiles/me`                          - upsert own companion profile (companion mode required)
  - `DELETE /api/profiles/me`                          - delete own companion profile (cascades availability)
  - `GET    /api/profiles/me/availability`             - list own windows
  - `POST   /api/profiles/me/availability`             - create a window
  - `PUT    /api/profiles/me/availability/[id]`        - patch a window
  - `DELETE /api/profiles/me/availability/[id]`        - delete a window
  - `PUT    /api/profiles/me/photo`                    - point avatar_path at an existing object under <userId>/
  - `DELETE /api/profiles/me/photo`                    - clear avatar_path
  - `GET    /api/profiles/[id]`                        - public companion view (RLS-gated to verified)

- **TypeScript wire shapes** (`app/api/profiles/_lib/types.ts`):
  - `OwnCompanionProfileDTO` - everything the owner's profile-setup
    screen needs in one round-trip; joins display_name/email/
    avatar_path from public.users.
  - `PublicCompanionProfileDTO` - what `/companions/[id]` renders;
    strips owner-only fields (no email, no Stripe ids); embeds the
    companion's full availability list.
  - `AvailabilityDTO` - one recurring weekly window.
  - Mappers `toOwnCompanionProfileDTO`, `toPublicCompanionProfileDTO`,
    `toAvailabilityDTO`. The Frontend agent should import these for
    response typing.

- **Error envelope** (`app/api/profiles/_lib/errors.ts`):
  - `{ error: { code, message, details? } }` - `code` is the stable
    `ApiErrorCode` union the Frontend can switch on; `details` is the
    `ZodError.flatten()` shape on validation failures.

- **What is NOT writable from this surface** (frozen as a non-feature):
  `verification_status`, `verified_at`, `stripe_connect_account_id`,
  `stripe_payouts_enabled`, `avg_rating`, `rating_count` on
  `companion_profiles` are owned by other agents and silently
  dropped from PUT bodies (zod schema does not include them).

MANUAL CHECKPOINTS

For the Orchestrator / Foundations / founder. None of these block more
Core-API code:

1. **Provision Supabase project envs.** `.env.local` still ships
   placeholders for `NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL`,
   `NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY`, and `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY`.
   Until those point at a real project, no `/api/profiles` request
   can be authorized end-to-end. Same blocker the Database and Auth
   agents flagged.

2. **Apply migrations to dev/staging** so the profiles module has the
   `companion_profiles` and `availability` tables (and the
   `companion_profiles_select_verified` RLS policy that backs the
   verification gate) actually present. Owner: Database agent /
   Foundations - the incantation is documented in
   `orchestration-logs/phase-1/Database_Agent.log` (manual checkpoint
   #3).

3. **Provision a disposable Supabase project for tests** and export
   `TEST_SUPABASE_URL` / `TEST_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY` /
   `TEST_SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY`. That unblocks the QA agent's
   `tests/integration/profiles.test.ts` (PUT/GET/DELETE round-trips
   against PostgREST) and `tests/rls/policies.test.ts` (verification
   gate, owner-only update fence). Same disposable-project requirement
   the Database agent's checkpoint #6 calls out.

4. **Storage bucket RLS for `avatars`** (owner: Database / Auth
   agents). The photo endpoint enforces the `<userId>/` prefix on the
   *path string*, but the storage bucket itself should also reject
   cross-prefix writes at the RLS layer so a compromised client cannot
   bypass the application check. Auth's checkpoint #3 lists the
   recommended policies.

5. **Open product decisions still routed to the founder via the
   Orchestrator** that touch this surface in later phases:
   - Platform fee % - affects Payments, not the profiles module.
   - Cancellation / refund policy - same.
   - Whether `bio_long` / `headline` should pass through a
     moderation/PII filter before publication (Trust & Safety).
   - Anonymous (signed-out) discovery on `GET /api/profiles/[id]` -
     today the route requires auth; relaxing that is a product call
     we did NOT make in this phase.
